.TH HELLO-GREET 1 "2025-12-16" "hello-greet 1.0"
.SH NAME
hello-greet \- localized greeting demo using libgreet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hello-greet
.RI [ --help ] " [NAME]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hello-greet
prints a localized greeting message using GNU gettext and the shared library
.BR libgreet .
If NAME is not provided, a default is used.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --help
Show help in English and Russian and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B APP_LOCALEDIR
Override locale directory (useful for running from build tree).
.TP
.B LANGUAGE
Standard gettext variable to pick language (e.g. ru_RU.UTF-8).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gettext (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Student assignment project
